    • Method Detail

      • getAppToken

        public java.lang.String getAppToken()
        The app token corresponding to your application.

        App tokens are issued on the SupportKit web portal. This value may only be set once, and must be set at init time.

        Returns:
        The app token

      • isAppWideGestureEnabled

        public boolean isAppWideGestureEnabled()
        A boolean property that indicates whether to enable the app-wide gesture (two-finger swipe down) to present the SupportKit UI.

        The default value is true.

        Returns:
        Is app wide gesture enabled

      • setAppWideGestureEnabled

        public void setAppWideGestureEnabled(boolean appWideGestureEnabled)
        A boolean property that indicates whether to enable the app-wide gesture (two-finger swipe down) to present the SupportKit UI.

        The default value is true.

        Parameters:
        appWideGestureEnabled - Is app wide gesture enabled

      • isGestureHintOnFirstLaunchEnabled

        public boolean isGestureHintOnFirstLaunchEnabled()
        A boolean property that indicates whether to show a hint on how to perform the app-wide gesture when SupportKit is launched for the first time (without using the gesture).

        The default value is true.

        Returns:
        Is gesture hint on first launch enabled

      • setGestureHintOnFirstLaunchEnabled

        public void setGestureHintOnFirstLaunchEnabled(boolean gestureHintOnFirstLaunchEnabled)
        A boolean property that indicates whether to show a hint on how to perform the app-wide gesture when SupportKit is launched for the first time (without using the gesture).

        The default value is true.

        Parameters:
        gestureHintOnFirstLaunchEnabled - Is gesture hint on first launch enabled
